<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-593-884  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 593 884.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Sept 4 1989 n264 p13(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC tells MCI to revise plan. (Federal Communications Commissionturns down MCI Communications Corp request for CALL USA connectionin Spain)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) denies the request ofMCI Communications Corp to provide a toll-free number access fromSpain to an operator in the US.andP;  It ordered MCI to revise itsproposal, concluding that the telephone company was using anon-uniform accounting rate without applying for the appropriatewaiver of international pricing policy.andP;  At the heart of theruling was the objection of rival ATandamp;T that MCI's CALL USA servicewas not sufficiently different from its USADIRECT service or otherinternational services.andP;  MCI protested the ruling, noting that theATandamp;T service was only available in trial service applications at10 locations in Spain, and that ATandamp;T had no comparable serviceoffering in Spain.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (cases)American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (cases).andO;Ticker:    T; MCIC.andO;Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionInternational CommunicationsTelephone CompaniesSpainPricing Policy.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>